article.description: Jhasmin Player and Melissa Jones each scored 13 points, Rachel Allison added 11, and Baylor (No. 9 ESPN/USA Today, No. 10 AP) beat Stephen F. Austin 77-42 on Friday night.
article.headline: Player scores eight points in decisive 28-1 first-half run to push No. 9 Baylor
article.linkText: No doubt about No. 9 Baylor after early 28-1 run
article.story:
WACO, Texas -- Jhasmin Player and Melissa Jones each scored 13 points, Rachel Allison added 11, and Baylor (No. 9 ESPN/USA Today, No. 10 AP) beat Stephen F. Austin 77-42 on Friday night.

Stephen F. Austin (2-1) scored first on Tammara Marion's jumper, but the Lady Bears then went on 28-1 run over the next 14 minutes to put away the game. Player scored eight points during the run, and Baylor (3-0) led 41-9 at halftime.

Whitney Cormier led SFA with 11 points. Ebony Alexander, who led the Ladyjacks with 13 points per game, was held to just three on 1-of-8 shooting.
